      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AT THE DISTANCE (2) comes here just three days after scoring by a neck over 1710m at Ballarat. Has the benefit of a good draw. His last-start form is good enough to win a race of this calibre. SPIRITED LASS (8) resumes from a spell of ten weeks after closing off last campaign in good form, the last run being a solid third over 2080m at this track. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Will have plenty of admirers. MISTA WALKER (5) is flying at present with three successive wins to his name, most recently at Warragul six days ago. Big chance to keep the ball rolling. SHAQ THE ANVIL (3) did a good job to finish in the minor placings two runs back then things went sour last time when he broke and finished a long way back in tenth over 1690m at Kilmore. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Beautifully placed and is able to make amends.",
